article.description: — Logan Johnson had 17 points as Saint Mary’s beat Pacific 58-46 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Johnson leads Saint Mary's (Calif.) over Pacific 58-46
article.linkText: Johnson leads Saint Mary's (Calif.) over Pacific 58-46
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- — Logan Johnson had 17 points as Saint Mary’s beat Pacific 58-46 on Thursday night. Matthias Tass had 15 points for Saint Mary’s (13-7, 4-5 West Coast Conference). Dan Fotu added nine rebounds and three blocks. Tommy Kuhse had six rebounds. Daniss Jenkins had 12 points for the Tigers (8-8, 5-7). Broc Finstuen added 11 points. Jordan Bell had 12 rebounds. Jeremiah Bailey, the Tigers’ second leading scorer entering the contest at 11 points per game, failed to make a shot (0 of 5) and was held scoreless. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
